It's Tax Day, and while most Americans are trying to get a refund, or simply scrounge together enough to pay their taxes, a group of millionaires is fighting to make sure they taxed a higher rate.
The Patriotic Millionaires believe it is their responsibility to pay more in taxes since they can afford to pay more.
Morris Pearl, former managing director of BlackRock, Inc., and chairman of the Patriotic Millionaires joins The Thom Hartmann Program to discuss why the wealthy should be taxed more than other groups.